# Trivy ignore policy — every entry here is a documented, deliberate risk
# acceptance, NOT a blanket gate disable. The CI Trivy jobs
# (pr-checks.yml / ci.yml) still fail the build on any HIGH/CRITICAL finding
# that is not explicitly listed below. Review this file whenever it's
# touched; each entry must keep its justification current.

# --- services/api-gateway (npm) ---
#
# CVE-2026-44902 — @opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node /
# @opentelemetry/sdk-node DoS via malformed HTTP request. Fixed only in the
# @opentelemetry/core v2.x line, which requires bumping every
# @opentelemetry/* package in this service in lockstep (v1 -> v2 is a
# breaking API change for the tracing SDK we rely on). That migration needs
# its own regression pass against services/api-gateway's tracing setup and
# is out of scope for this CI-wiring change. Tracked as follow-up work.
CVE-2026-44902

# CVE-2026-25223 — fastify Content-Type validation bypass. Fixed only in
# fastify v5 (major bump from the v4 this service is pinned to), which is a
# breaking change to route/schema/hook APIs used throughout src/. Requires a
# dedicated migration + regression pass, out of scope here. Tracked as
# follow-up work.
CVE-2026-25223

# --- services/api-gateway image (node:20-slim base, Debian 12) ---
# --- services/orders image (python:3.12-slim base, Debian 13) ---
#
# The findings below are OS packages / npm-cli-bundled dependencies baked
# into the official Debian-based `node:20-slim` / `python:3.12-slim` base
# images — not code these services execute (no shell, perl, tar, gzip,
# util-linux, or npm-cli invocation happens at runtime; the runtime stage
# only runs `node dist/index.js` / `python -m app.main`). The great majority
# have Status "fixed=None" — no upstream Debian security patch exists yet,
# so there is nothing to bump to. The few with an available fix
# (libcap2, libgnutls30, and the npm-cli-bundled cross-spawn/glob/
# minimatch/sigstore/tar under the "Node.js" target) ship inside the base
# image itself, not in this repo's package-lock.json, so they can only be
# picked up by a base-image refresh, not a dependency bump here. Re-run this
# scan on each base-image bump (Dependabot/renovate on the FROM lines is a
# good follow-up) and drop entries here once the upstream image is patched.
CVE-2026-53615
CVE-2026-41992
CVE-2026-54369
CVE-2026-4878
CVE-2026-33845
CVE-2026-33846
CVE-2026-3833
